Zanzibar President, Hussein Ali Mwinyi has appointed Ambassador Mohammed Mwinyi Mzale as the new Ethics Commissioner  in the President’s office, Constitution and Legal Affairs, Public Service Management and Good Governance. A statement released by the Isle’s Chief of Secretary, Engineer Zena Said on Friday stated that his appointment is effective from today (February 18, 2022). Ambassador Mzale started his diplomatic career in 1992, after one year in the position of the Minister of Education of Zanzibar. In 1993 - 2002, he served as Tanzania's ambassador to Egypt, and in 2002 - 2006, in Saudi Arabia. In 2010 to 2014 he served as ambassador to Stockholm, Sweden where he was also accredited to Denmark, Finland, Norway, Iceland, Estonia, Latvia, Ukraine and Lithuania. Before being commissioned to Sweden, he worked as the Director of the Near East Department in Tanzania's Ministry of Foreign Affairs and International Cooperation.